name: FedEx and UPS Airbus A300-600Rs Depart Calgary Airport
description:
It's not every day you see two A300s departing at the same time (except maybe in Memphis or Louisville)! Here we have two examples of Airbus' first widebody from Calgary's two major American couriers taxiing up close on Bravo and departing runway 17L for their respective destinations. Both crews waved as well! ATC is included, enjoy.

Thanks for watching!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

FLIGHT INFORMATION
Airline: UPS (UPS/5X) / FedEx (FDX/FX)
Aircraft: Airbus A300F4-622R(F) / Airbus A300B4-622R(F)
Flight Number: 5X6491 / FX141
Engines: 2x Pratt and Whitney PW4158 (both)
Registration: N131UP / N728FD
Route: Calgary (YYC) - Louisville (SDF) / Calgary (YYC) - Memphis (MEM)
Callsign: UPS 6491 heavy / FEDEX 141 heavy
Runway used: 17L
Date filmed: July 2018
Local time: 1800
